The Needhay project is a NoSQL solution for writing and reading assets which do not belong in a RDBMS.

	Needle
		Container for $x number of $type collections
		
	Needle Collection $type
		Container for $x number of pointer collections
		
	Pointer Collection
		Container for $x number pointers
		
	Pointer
		Name of the asset as stored on the filesystem (haystack)
		
	Haystack
		Where all the assets are stored. Filesystem.
		
	Adapter
		Needle files can be stored in a variety of ways
			File
				Yaml (not yet implemented)
				Xml
			Database
				MySQL (not yet implemented)
				
	Asset
		The file which a pointer will point to. Example assets are images and descriptions (html files).
				
	
